  "_comment": "Total mean lifetime in ticks (20/tick·sec, 24000 = 1 in-game day) — average time from fresh to fully spoiled. default_food_ticks covers any edible item with no explicit entry (~2 days). Cooked food keeps ~6 days, processed/preserved goods longer. Food carries a freshness LEVEL (Fresh/Bland), not a clock, so it stacks; spoilage is a per-second probabilistic roll whose average matches these times. COOKING_PLAN.md.",
  "_comment_phases": "bland_fraction = the share of the lifetime spent BLAND (half food value) before spoiling; the rest is FRESH. salt_life_multiplier = how many times longer salted food keeps.",
